SECTION 3 — RESTRICTIONS ON USE
================================================================================

3.1   Without the Author's explicit prior written authorization, You must NOT:

      (a)  Deploy, execute, run, or host the Backend Application or any portion
           thereof on any computing infrastructure for any purpose;

      (b)  Copy, clone, fork, mirror, or reproduce the Backend Application or
           any portion thereof in any form or medium;

      (c)  Distribute, transfer, publish, sublicense, sell, or otherwise make
           the Backend Application or any portion thereof available to any third
           party;

      (d)  Modify, adapt, translate, extend, refactor, or create any Derivative
           Work based on the Backend Application, including reimplementing the
           Data Models, Cryptographic License System, or API Surface;

      (e)  Reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or attempt to reconstruct
           the Cryptographic License System, the HMAC key verification logic,
           the domain hash algorithm, or any other security or business logic
           in the Backend Application;

      (f)  Access, query, inspect, scrape, or interact with the API Surface of
           the Hosted Service through any means other than the official frontend
           application, except as explicitly authorized in writing by the Author;

      (g)  Conduct or commission Penetration Testing, vulnerability assessment,
           security scanning, load testing, stress testing, or any other form
           of systematic technical probing of the Hosted Service without the
           Author's explicit prior written authorization;

      (h)  Attempt to access, read, modify, or interfere with the Backend
           Application's databases, message queues, caches, file storage
           systems, or any other data persistence layer;

      (i)  Use the Backend Application's source code as training data for any
           machine learning model, AI code assistant, or automated software
           generation system;

      (j)  Circumvent, disable, tamper with, or reverse engineer any security
           mechanism in the Backend Application, including the trafficGuard
           middleware, rate limiters, JWT authentication, bcrypt password
           hashing, the white-label heartbeat verification, or the maintenance
           guard;

      (k)  Use the Data Models or schema designs as the basis for any competing
           event management platform or similar application;

      (l)  Remove, alter, or obscure any copyright notices, license notices,
           or proprietary markings embedded in the Backend Application;

      (m)  Use any portion of the Backend Application for Commercial Use without
           a separate written commercial license agreement with the Author.

3.2   Unauthorized API Access. Any attempt to directly access, query, or
      interact with the Backend Application's API endpoints outside of the
      officially supported frontend application — including through Postman,
      curl, automated scripts, SDK clients, or any other HTTP client — without
      explicit written authorization from the Author constitutes a breach of
      this Agreement.

3.3   Security Research. If You discover a security vulnerability in the Hosted
      Service or Backend Application, You must promptly report it to the Author
      at planit.userhelp@gmail.com without disclosing it publicly, exploiting
      it, or using it for any purpose other than the report itself. Responsible
      disclosure does not grant You any license rights beyond those in Section 2.

