SECTION 4 — CRYPTOGRAPHIC LICENSE SYSTEM
================================================================================

4.1   The Cryptographic License System embedded in the Backend Application is
      a proprietary invention of the Author and constitutes one of the most
      commercially sensitive trade secrets in the Software.

4.2   You acknowledge that the key format, the HMAC chain algorithm, the domain
      hash function, the expiry encoding method, and the verification logic
      collectively form a proprietary system that the Author uses to enforce
      white-label licensing terms and protect commercial revenue.

4.3   Any attempt to reverse engineer, reproduce, bypass, spoof, or otherwise
      circumvent the Cryptographic License System constitutes: (a) a material
      breach of this Agreement; (b) misappropriation of trade secrets; and
      (c) a potential violation of computer fraud and abuse laws in applicable
      jurisdictions.

4.4   The WL_LICENSE_SECRET environment variable and all related cryptographic
      secrets are the Author's confidential information. You have no right to
      access, derive, or reconstruct these secrets under any circumstances.

